lead_paragraph: Stephen Strasburg was removed from a no-hit bid after 6 2/3 innings Sunday by Washington manager Dusty Baker, and Ramon Cabrera singled against Matt Belisle leading off the eighth for Cincinnati's first hit.

headline.print_headline: After Strasburg Leaves No-Hit Bid, Reds Get Single in 8th
